  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class SameExclusiveBoundsException
extends InvalidRangeException
    Exception for Range in case the lower and upper bounds are exclusive and of the same value. 
    final Bound<Integer> lowerBound = Bound.exclusive(4);
final Bound<Integer> upperBound = lowerBound;
assertThatThrownBy(() -> range(lowerBound, upperBound)).isInstanceOf(SameExclusiveBoundsException.class);

    See the test code.
